      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DEFIANCE (3) resumed in a strong Maiden with a tiring fifth over 1100m at Hawkesbury after sitting on the fast tempo. Comes back to the 1000m here and will take catching around the tight Wyong track. Go close. BRUCE I AM (1) Star Turn gelding from the good producing mare Crystal Rock on debut for the Joe Pride yard. Has looked strong in all four trials and maps to get the right run. Can sprint well first-up. DENISE'S GAL (8) all four runs have been okay and resumes from the inside draw. Finished sixth in a tight contest over 1100m at Gosford on January 9. Fitter after a recent trial win with the key jockey change. Leading contender. WEEKEND MARKET (7) lightly raced mare resuming. Had mixed luck in her first prep and fitted with the one good trial placing over 816m at Warwick Farm.",
